# ============================================================================
# AUTHENTICATION NOTE FOR DEVELOPMENT
# ============================================================================
# In Development mode (ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Development):
#   - Authentication is DISABLED for easy testing
#   - You do NOT need to include the Authorization header
#   - All API endpoints are accessible without a token
#
# In Production mode:
#   - Authentication is ENABLED
#   - You MUST include a valid Bearer token in the Authorization header
#   - Use format: Authorization: Bearer <your-token-here>
#
# To test with authentication enabled:
#   1. Set ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Production
#   2. Include the @AuthToken header (shown above) with requests
# ============================================================================ ============================================================================
### HEALTH CHECK (No Authentication Required)
### ============================================================================

### Check API Health Status
GET {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/health
Accept: application/json

###

### ============================================================================
### GET REQUESTS - Retrieve Users
### ============================================================================

### Get All Users - Returns list of all active users
GET {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Specific User by ID - Replace {id} with actual user ID (e.g., 1)
GET {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users/1
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### ============================================================================
### POST REQUEST - Create New User
### ============================================================================

### Create a New User - Requires valid user data with all required fields
POST {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Wilson",
  "email": "bob.wilson@techhive.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1-555-0104",
  "jobTitle": "DevOps Engineer",
  "department": "Infrastructure"
}

###

### ============================================================================
### PUT REQUEST - Update Existing User
### ============================================================================

### Update User Details - Replace {id} with actual user ID (e.g., 1)
PUT {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users/1
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe Updated",
  "email": "john.doe.updated@techhive.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1-555-0105",
  "jobTitle": "Principal Engineer",
  "department": "Engineering"
}

###

### ============================================================================
### DELETE REQUEST - Remove User
### ============================================================================

### Delete User - Performs soft delete (marks as inactive)
### Replace {id} with actual user ID (e.g., 1)
DELETE {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users/1
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}

###

### ============================================================================
### ERROR SCENARIO EXAMPLES
### ============================================================================

### Example: Unauthorized Request (Missing Token)
GET {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users
Accept: application/json

###

### Example: Retrieve Non-Existent User
GET {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users/9999
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Example: Invalid Email Format - Will Return 400 Bad Request
POST {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid User",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "phoneNumber": "+1-555-0106",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering"
}

###

### Example: Duplicate Email - Will Return 400 Bad Request
POST {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Duplicate John",
  "email": "john.doe@techhive.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1-555-0107",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering"
}

###

### Example: Missing Required Field - Will Return 400 Bad Request
POST {{User_Management_API_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: {{AuthToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Incomplete User",
  "email": "incomplete@techhive.com"
}

###
